The paper discusses the Provenance, Authoring and Versioning ontology (PAV) for tracking the provenance, authoring, and versioning of web resources, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The ontology is particularly useful for scientific content, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.DB (databases) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) that deal with scientific data and knowledge representation. The paper also mentions the use of PAV in tracking computational workflows, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DL (digital libraries) and cs.IR (information retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the interoperability of PAV with other ontologies, which is relevant to sub-category cs.SE (software engineering).
